  "text": "The function ψ and the speed w play the same role as here. The unknown r = r(t, x; w) is the probability density of vehicles having maximal speed w that at time t are at point x. In (3.3) there is one function to be specified, ψ, as in (1.4). The parameters are R (which is normalized to 1 in [CITATION_1] ),w andŵ, similarly to (1.4). Since no limit speed is there defined, no parameter in (3.3) has the same role as here V max .",
